\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 2.3.3	
\f0 Replica Manager\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl360\slmult1\sa240\qj\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs24 \cf0 The Replica Manager (RM) is responsible for tracing the different active Replicas on the DPSS system. The main job of the RM is a communication with the Leader. For example, if any Replica generates a wrong result, then the Leader informs the RM the status of this Replica. The RM maintains a failure counter for each Replica. This counter is incremented for each wrong Replica result. If the counter reaches three failures, the Replica Manager will replace the corresponding replica with a new one.
\fs22 \
\
