\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 2.3.4	
\f0 Request Handler\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl360\slmult1\sa240\qj\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs24 \cf0 The Request Handler is the component that translates and manages the request broadcasted from the FE. Request Handler module is implemented in the same host where the Leader is. The module receives the requests via UDP/IP from the FE and uses FIFO technique to process them iteratively. As several of these requests may have been sent in a random order from the FE, the Request Handler is responsible for arranging the received requests. The received requests are processed and ordered based sequence number assigned to it by the FE before sending. The Leader will then multicast each request to the other two Replicas and also processes the request locally. After getting the results from other Replicas, the Leader will compare all three results and send the most returned result to the FE. This is done for each request received iteratively. Moreover, if any of the Replicas generates a wrong result, the Request Handler will inform the RM.
